# Frontend Contract Rules

## Data access

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — direct fetch or invented shapes
const res = await fetch("http://localhost:8000/api/v1/orders/1");
type Order = { orderId: string; totalPrice: number };

// ✅ GOOD — contract hooks + shared types
import { useOrder } from "@/lib/hooks";
import type { OutcomeOrder } from "@/lib/types";
const { data: order, isLoading } = useOrder(orderId);
```

- All shapes come from `@/lib/types` (snake_case fields, mirrors backend JSON).
- All data flows through `@/lib/hooks` → `@/lib/api`. Never hardcode fixture data inside components — extend `lib/mock-data.ts` instead.
- New endpoint? Add it to `lib/api.ts` with both mock and real branches, then a hook in `lib/hooks.ts`.

## Status display

Use the dual-language maps from `@/lib/state-labels` — clients and workers see different words for the same state. Never show workers' failure states (`rework`) to clients.

## Styling

- Design tokens only: `bg-background`, `text-primary`, `border-border`, `text-muted-foreground`. No hardcoded hex.
- Light + dark must both work (`.dark` class on `<html>`).

## Ownership

`app/**` and `components/**` are v0's lane (branch `main`). If you're a Cursor agent on `core`, limit UI edits to wiring existing components to hooks — don't redesign screens.
